From cou.: 50 H
From Soup: 50 Note that real receptor- ligand interactions are anisotropic in nature and that this anisotropy will affect the binding geometry. However, to reduce the unreasonable computational cost, in this work we employed a coarse-grained model and the anisotropy of the receptor- ligand interaction is ignored. Specifically, in order to avoid the aggregation of the transmembrane receptors, the interaction parameters were set to a R H R H = a R T R T = 50. To describe the strong binding interaction between ligands and mobile receptors, the receptor- ligand interaction was set to ε LR H = 0.0. Furthermore, the nanoparticle and the ligands are thought to be hydrophobic, and thus their interaction with solvent were set to a PW = a LW = 80. Although some atomistic details were sacrificed during this coarse-graining procedure, the essential features of the system are reproduced by the simulation model and the parameter set.
